Package: SpatialDataR
Title: Native R Interface to the SpatialData Zarr Format for Spatial
    Omics
Version: 0.99.0
Authors@R:
    person("Cuiwei", "Gao", email = "48gaocuiwei@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"),
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0000-0000-0000"))
Description: Provides native R infrastructure for inspecting and
    reading SpatialData-formatted Zarr stores without Python
    dependencies. Discovers and references images, labels,
    points, shapes, and annotation tables stored in '.zarr'
    directories. Includes element-level readers for Zarr arrays
    (via 'Rarr' or 'pizzarr'), CSV and Parquet point tables
    (via 'arrow'), and coordinate system transformations.
    Designed as a lightweight bridge between the Python
    'SpatialData' ecosystem and R/Bioconductor spatial analysis
    workflows.
